Miami Art Basel Week was extra special this year 🪢 Thank you @thecultivist @jimmychoo and @harpersbazaarus for cohosting an unforgettable evening at the residence of @ivanaberendika 🤍 and inviting me to be a part of it by activating the space with my work! ✨ And special thank you to @kirbyfkane for all of your support, expertise and kindness! ✨💐

I also need to thank @cheeks.clt for making the drive down to Miami with me in a completely packed to the brim car and helping me install everything. Thank you to @abigailogilvy for your support and lending the Welcome Fence for its fourth debut as well as Life Source which was a part of the suspended installation! And thank you to @__luvdestiny and @art_bycal for making the push to create everything possible 💛

It was a great evening of meeting new friends and being so overjoyed just watching people interact with my work in such a beautiful setting. 

It really takes a lot of people to make it happen 💛💛💛

패브릭 디자이너 @fiberess 와의 두번째 콜라보 촬영! 며칠전 플로리다에서 전시회를 마치고 온 그녀의 몇몇 작품들을 촬영하게 되었는데, 촬영내내 너무 재미있고 유쾌하게 진행되어서 시간이 어떻게 흐르는지도 몰랐다. 한땀한땀 그녀의 정성으로 가득한 핸드메이드 작품들이 좋은 클라이언트들을 만나 좋은 곳으로 갔으면 좋겠다.

Feliz Noche Buena, I hope everyone has a restful and happy holiday ✨ Thank you for following my work and for supporting artists. 

I’m looking forward to being back in Panamá next week and spending new year’s with my family. (I also can’t wait to escape this cold weather!) Look at the cute faux fireplace at my grandmother’s house lol 🌴🌺🎄🌞🦜 

What are you looking forward to this season or new year? 

Photos by @m00s0sic 📸

🛠I am THRILLED to finally share that we have been creating this massive Woven Installation for @loweshomeimporvement! Located over the 24th, 23rd and 22nd floor of the new Lowe’s Tech Hub in Charlotte NC these pieces cascade down through the floor levels, the warp and weft shifting colors as you move through the space ✨I can’t describe how it feels to see these finally up, hanging vertically and in the beautiful space they were created to occupy. After almost two years since the conception of this work I have @wearegokotta, @artpopstreetgallery and the very cool team at Lowe’s tech Hub to thank for making this extroardinary Inspiration Project possible! My contruction and installtion team also deserves the biggest shout out! Thank you @art_bycal , @cheeks.clt and @__luvdestiny for making it possible to bring this work into reality. I could not have done it without you 💛💛💛

I have much more to share with you!

@m00s0sic as always you killed it on the 📸 thank you my friend! 🔥

Did you know you can touch the art? A closer inspection achieves a more intimate exchange as @fiberess allows visitors to physically engage with the work through the sense of touch. “I really enjoy when people can touch the Magnified Weavings I make,” says Sánchez, “sometimes, some spaces insist that people refrain from touching any of the artwork, but it’s often one of the first things I hear from people, ‘I just want to touch it!’ and I think it is really satisfying when they can. It’s fulfilling that curiosity, sense of play and tactility. That for me is important for the work; letting the viewer indulge in that desire to feel and explore the work through another sense. It also breaks a barrier between myself as the artist with the viewer by enabling them to experience the work in a way like I do. The work is plush and flexible, it gets pushed and pulled and even sat on in the studio and it’s not very fragile so I feel like, why safeguard that experience for only myself or some people?”

Visit “Mending Joy” to experience the work in person.

“Hug Me” is a new work that feels like it expresses itself in my place. Through the shape, size, feel and colors its designed for an embrace. In reality, receiving a hug or giving an embrace has the potential for a range of emotions. We know many reasons why. We hug when we are excited, greeting, being polite, fulfilling expectations, comforting, feeling sad, grieving, saying goodbye, saying I love you. 
As someone who can often struggle with personal touch and affection it’s a complicated experience. It feels kind of strange and uncomfortable but I’ve created this object that shamelessly says “hug me”, it’s almost a kind of body double. It feels like a permanent vulnerability. It’s something outside of me that’s now soaking in the world as it leans against the gallery wall, observing and dripping a tender energy.”

Solo Exhibition- Mending Joy
@abigailogilvy gallery in Boston

¡What an insanely memorable week!💖 I’m honored to have worked with @taskforce.us @mtv and @active_minds to help activate the launch of their new mental health campaign A.S.K during the @vmas with these GIANT FRIENDSHIP BRACELETS. We had a blast setting up for the Vma’s block party and then for the event itself, and we got to see Shakira, Karol G, and so many more perform 🫠✨

It feels incredibly special to be a part of this project to help create bonds and teach one another how we can support each other through tough times. 

Thank you sooo much to my crew who made this installation possible on a time crunch @art_bycal @cheeks.clt @__luvdestiny @qn.vu @jordy_eng I 💖 you guys. And thank you to everyone in @taskforce.us and @active_minds for believing in and supporting my vision. You are an incredible group and I hope to cross paths again!
